2022
What a year 💗
Swipe to the end and you’ll see holiday Barbie ✨

I don’t know how I got so lucky to have friends like these! I love looking over all the fun memories  made in a year but these people were there for all the other days. All the hard days when I wanted to quit and all the sad days when I wanted to hide inside and cry. They showed me what friendship really means and they SHOWED UP for me this past year. No matter if we hung out every week or every six months, the support from them kept me going. I just wanna say I LOVE Y’ALL SO MUCH! ♥️♥️
(Missing a very important person, Julian)
31 days of highs and lows ✨

I don’t have the words to explain how honored and excited I am to be playing Eva Perón at @americanrep and @shakespeareindc !!
Working with this entire company is a DREAM! 
Thank you everyone for all the love today 💕
Come out to Cambridge and DC to see us!

Also I would be remiss if I didn’t say that I know how complex and personal this story is to so many people. I’m looking forward to diving into the complexity of it and handling the storytelling with care ❤️
#evita #evitarevival

It’s was an absolute honor to perform for @im.angelabassett and @courtneybvance tonight. Two absolute legends!
Scroll to see a picture of Angela Bassett and 10 year old Shereen 💕
I’m just feeling so blessed after this long performance week!
Video- @ericanthonylopezofficial
I looked at a pretty garden for hours 🤍

It’s not goodbye, just a see you later ❤️
Sad we didn’t get to do our final weekend but so thankful for the past few months with this show.
Taking on such an iconic show is thrilling and daunting. The person who said it best was America Ferrera. “Like, we have to always be extraordinary, but somehow we’re always doing it wrong.” But with every obstacle came a lesson. The biggest one was that nothing will ever be perfect. Once in a blue moon everything will align and things will go exactly as planned. The rest of the time you try to remember that you have a really cool job and you dreamed of being in this spot as a kid. We get to play dress up for a living!  How cool is that!
So I hit pause on this chapter and get a month to reflect, cherish the memories, and get a lot of much needed sleep. 🤍
Hope to see y’all in DC!

All gold at @elmagopopoficial ‘s opening night on Broadway ✨

social_posts.post_text:
Monday was my birthday so I’m a little late on posting this!
I’m so thankful to have been able to usher in a new year this way. It’s an honor to perform this show every night (even when my body tells me it wants to get back in bed and take a break lol) but it’s thrilling when someone sees the show and then ask to do a piece on your performance!
Thank you to the entire company on this project! It takes a village to put up a project like this.
I can’t believe this chapter is getting ready to come to an end! ❤️🤍
Link in bio for the full thing!

“Don’t cry for me Argentina… The truth is I shall not leave you. Though it may get harder for you to see me. I’m Argentina and always will be.”

As this journey comes to an end I have to reflect on how grateful I am. This role was one I always dreamed of, but never thought I would be awarded the fortune of doing it. Joining the legacy of women who have donned the white ball gown is no easy feat. This role challenged me as a performer and as a human being. There were good days and bad ones, but as I said my final goodbye to Buenos Aires last night I was filled with joy. Joy to have built this show with a wonderful creative team, cast and crew, both at ART and STC. Joy to have my work husband, @caesarsamayoa ! To know him is to love him and I couldn’t imagine going on this journey with anyone else. Joy to have been able to share it with the wonderful audiences in Boston and DC. Finally, joy to see what the universe will surprise me with next!
Goodnight & Thank you Evita ❤️🤍

“I know what I have to do… but I don’t know if I have the strength to do it”
Happy Halloween ❤️❤️
